<item>
            <title>[LU-12101] lctl push causes a crash</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12101</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The command: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;lctl --net tcp push&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;will cause a host with any active lustre connections to crash.&#160; Code in &lt;tt&gt;ksocknal_push()&lt;/tt&gt; has an incorrect termination condition and falls off the end of a linked lists, dereferencing an invalid pointer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Precise results vary.&#160; e.g. an LASSERT failure in ksocknal_connsock_addref(), or a NULL pointer dereference.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Tested on SLE15 + Lustre 2.11, and drivers/staging.</environment>
